OL,3,CNetwork Rail warns people are 'risking
OL,4,Cit all' at level crossings
OL,6,FThirty years later, she has turned her
OL,7,Fexperience into positive action by
OL,8,Fsuccessfully campaigning for an
OL,9,Faccessible footbridge at the same
OL,10,Fstation and highlighting the
OL,11,Fimportance of safety at level
OL,12,Fcrossings to raise awareness and
OL,13,Fprevent similar accidents.
OL,15,FLucy said: "The consequences of a
OL,16,Fsplit-second decision can be life-
OL,17,Faltering. I know this all too well
OL,18,Ffrom my own accident.
